---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---
<SiteLayout
  title="Cookies — Pumpa"
  description="Pumpa sets no cookies. Here's exactly what is stored in your browser and why."
  surface="reading"
>
  <div class="page-head">
    <p class="mono-label">Cookies</p>
    <h1>No cookies. Really.</h1>
  </div>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      Pumpa doesn't set cookies, and there is no tracking, analytics or advertising
      script on this site today. What Pumpa does use is your browser's
      <code>localStorage</code> — a small store that never leaves your device and is
      never sent to any server.
    </p>
    <h2>What's in that storage</h2>
    <p>
      Your logged trips and fill-ups, your unit and currency preferences, a manually
      set fuel price, your Pro unlock, and your theme choice. That's the complete
      list. Clearing this site's data in your browser removes all of it — export a
      CSV first if you want a backup.
    </p>
    <h2>If this ever changes</h2>
    <p>
      If advertising is added to the free tier in the future, this page and the
      <a href="/privacy/">privacy page</a> will describe exactly what it involves
      before it ships.
    </p>
  </div>
</SiteLayout>
